Package: ubuntu-handheld
Version: 1.1-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: ubuntu-handheld contributors <ubuntu-handheld@localhost>
Installed-Size: 31
Depends: gamescope, sxhkd, acpi-call-dkms, python3-venv, python3-dev, python3-pip, build-essential, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, curl, gdm3, libfuse2t64, libhidapi-hidraw0, udev
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Handheld Ubuntu Setup (Ubuntu Game Session)
 Transforms an Ubuntu installation into a console-like handheld gaming
 experience. Installs and configures:
  - Ubuntu Game Session: Gamescope Steam Gamepad UI as the default boot session
    (a Steam OS-like experience)
  - Handheld Daemon (HHD) for TDP and controller management
  - HHD overlay for in-game quick access
  - Seamless switching between Ubuntu Game Session and Ubuntu desktop
  - Virtual keyboard for touchscreen / handheld input
 .
 Remove the package to fully revert to original Ubuntu behaviour.
